## üéØ USAGE GUIDELINES

### Do's ‚úì

**Typography:**
- ‚úì Use monospace font consistently across all text
- ‚úì Maintain wide letter spacing for headings
- ‚úì Keep all caps for headings and CTAs
- ‚úì Respect the 65-character line length for readability

**Color:**
- ‚úì Use Lello as the primary accent sparingly for maximum impact
- ‚úì Maintain high contrast between text and backgrounds
- ‚úì Use the stone gray background as your primary canvas
- ‚úì Allow generous whitespace around colored elements

**Layout:**
- ‚úì Embrace sharp corners and geometric precision
- ‚úì Maintain consistent 8px spacing increments
- ‚úì Keep layouts grid-aligned and structured
- ‚úì Use the sidebar navigation for primary site navigation

**3D Objects:**
- ‚úì Feature high-quality rendered objects prominently
- ‚úì Use consistent lighting across all 3D elements
- ‚úì Maintain the Lello color family for cohesion
- ‚úì Create clear drop shadows for depth

### Don'ts ‚úó

**Typography:**
- ‚úó Don't use serif or sans-serif fonts
- ‚úó Don't use thin font weights (under 400)
- ‚úó Don't use mixed case for headings
- ‚úó Don't exceed 75 characters per line

**Color:**
- ‚úó Don't use Lello for body text (poor readability)
- ‚úó Don't add unnecessary colors outside the palette
- ‚úó Don't use gradients on text
- ‚úó Don't use pure white as primary background

**Layout:**
- ‚úó Don't use rounded corners on primary elements
- ‚úó Don't break the 8px spacing system
- ‚úó Don't overcrowd the interface with too many elements
- ‚úó Don't hide the monospace character aesthetic with icon fonts

**3D Objects:**
- ‚úó Don't use low-poly or wireframe styles (inconsistent)
- ‚úó Don't mix photography with 3D renders
- ‚úó Don't use soft, blurry shadows
- ‚úó Don't add lens flares or over-processed effects

---

## üõ†Ô∏è IMPLEMENTATION NOTES

### Performance Considerations

**Font Loading:**
- Monospace fonts are system fonts (fast)
- No web font loading required
- Instant text rendering

**CSS:**
- Use CSS custom properties for easy theming
- Minimize use of box-shadow (performance cost)
- Prefer transforms over position changes
- Use `will-change` sparingly

### Browser Support

**Target Browsers:**
- Chrome/Edge: Last 2 versions
- Firefox: Last 2 versions
- Safari: Last 2 versions
- Mobile Safari: Last 2 versions
- Mobile Chrome: Last 2 versions

**Fallbacks:**
- CSS Grid with flexbox fallback
- Custom properties with fallback values
- Modern CSS with graceful degradation

### Asset Organization

```
/assets
  /images
    /3d-objects
      - cylinder-01.webp
      - sphere-rainbow.webp
      - geometric-assembly-01.webp
    /ascii-art
      - dojo-slug-logo.svg
    /icons
      - (minimal use, prefer unicode)
  /styles
    - variables.css
    - reset.css
    - typography.css
    - components.css
    - layout.css
    - utilities.css
  /scripts
    - navigation.js
    - interactions.js
```

